'''''Star Wars Insider'' 77''' is the seventy-seventh issue of ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine. It was released to newsstands on [[August 3]], [[2004]]. This marked the first ''Star Wars Insider'' issue published by [[IDG Entertainment]] as well as the first overseen by chief editor [[Brett Rector]].

Beginning with issue 77, ''Star Wars Insider'' implemented the fan newsletter ''[[Bantha Tracks (department)|Bantha Tracks]]'' as a regular department of the magazine, and also introduced with each new issue exclusive supplementary content online through the [[StarWars.com]] [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club|Hyperspace]] feature.

==Contents==
===Departments===
*"Letter from the Editor" {{C|by [[Brett Rector]]}}
*"[[Comlink (department)|Comlink]]"
*''[[Bantha Tracks (department)|Bantha Tracks]]'' Vol. 8
*"[[Skywalking]]" {{C|by Brett Rector and [[Benjamin Harper]]}}
*"[[Best of Hyperspace]]"
*"[[Scouting the Galaxy]]" &mdash; Elliot Finds My Holy Grail—And Gets It Free! {{C|by [[Stephen J. Sansweet|Steve Sansweet]]}}
*"[[Jabba's Collection]]" &mdash; What's Old Is New Again: The OTC Collection {{C|by starwars.hasbro.com}}
*"[[Drawn by the Force]]" &mdash; [[Republic 68|Clash of the Titans]] {{C|by [[Daniel Wallace]]}}
*"[[Jedi Library (department)|Jedi Library]]" &mdash; [[The Cestus Deception|Attack of the Clone Consciences]] {{C|by [[Jason Fry]]}}
*"[[Anchorhead Arcade]]" &mdash; ''Star Wars'' Battlefront {{C|by [[Frank Parisi]] and [[Hugh Sterbakov]]}}
*"[[Star Wars Q&A|Ask the Master]]" {{C|by Pablo Hidalgo}}
*"[[Laugh It Up, Fuzzball]]" {{C|by [[Francis Mao]]}}

===Features===
*"[[Prequel Update]] for Episode III" {{C|by [[Jane Irene Kelly]]}}
*:<small>In June, the Episode III post-production team completed their second cut of the film. Meanwhile, Wookies invaded the set in Sydney, Australia.</small>
*"[[Top Tension: The 10 Greatest Moments of The Classic Trilogy]]" {{C|by [[Dan Amrich]]}}
*:<small>Fans have debated ever since 1983 about which scenes in the classic trilogy are the greatest. See if your favorite moment or moments is included within and then let the debates rage on.</small>
*"[[Changing Seasons]] Part II: People of the Guardian" {{C|by [[Timothy Zahn]]}}
*:<small>In the story's conclusion, Obi-Wan Kenobi and Anakin Skywalker find themselves on a mission to stop an escalating Separatist threat.</small>

